        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-22 13:26:01.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n> \n> > Patch Set 1: Verified+1\n> > \n> > There is one caveat, it installs docker-ce (newest). we don't know which one that actually is, if it is run from molecule. But it seems to work.\n> \n> I again urge to use the same exact version as on target platform. This statement was supported by merging this patch: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/oom/offline-installer/+/86528\n\nI agree, but:\n- on target platform you install a correct version, because correct version is in resources.\n- on molecule you install newer, if prepare-docker-dind would install older one, youm install would probably upgrade it anyway, so then you need docker version stored both in datalists and in docker role itself...?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
