          "email": "b.grzybowski@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "bgrzybowski"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-23 07:23:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I agree, but:\n> - on target platform you install a correct version, because correct version is in resources.\n> - on molecule you install newer, if prepare-docker-dind would install older one, youm install would probably upgrade it anyway, so then you need docker version stored both in datalists and in docker role itself...?\n\nIn docker role 'yum' is called with 'state: present', that doesn't upgrade the package. 'state: latest' would.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
